# scripts/tool-versions.env — SINGLE SOURCE for the pinned dev-tool versions.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These versions were duplicated across .github/workflows/ci.yml (the `env:` block)
# and .pre-commit-config.yaml (`rev:` fields) with nothing keeping them in step.
# This file is now canonical and read by all three consumers:
#   • .github/workflows/ci.yml — a "Load pinned tool versions" step cats this into
#     $GITHUB_ENV, so CI installs exactly these (no version literals left in ci.yml).
#   • scripts/setup.sh (`make setup`) — local hermetic bootstrap installs/audits to
#     these same versions, so a contributor's box matches CI.
#   • scripts/audit-core.sh — a version-consistency section asserts the .pre-commit
#     hook revs still equal these (pre-commit YAML can't read this file dynamically,
#     so it's gated instead — drift fails the audit).
#
# Bump a version HERE and it propagates (ci + setup) or is enforced (pre-commit).
# Plain KEY=VALUE, no spaces around `=`, no `v` prefix — so this both `source`s in
# bash AND appends straight to $GITHUB_ENV.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SHELLCHECK_VERSION=0.10.0
LUACHECK_VERSION=1.2.0
NVIM_VERSION=0.12.3
MARKDOWNLINT_VERSION=0.22.1
ACTIONLINT_VERSION=1.7.8
GITLEAKS_VERSION=8.30.1
PRECOMMIT_VERSION=4.0.1
PRECOMMIT_HOOKS_VERSION=5.0.0
